# Autonomous execution

Agents MUST execute autonomously: investigate, implement, test, and report. Treat "work autonomously" in the PO message as the default mode.

## Required behavior

- Read the repo's root [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) before substantive edits. In the flows cornerstone repo, also read [CONTRIBUTING.md](../../CONTRIBUTING.md) (flows-only; not installed to product repos).
- Run terminal commands and tools yourself — do not instruct the PO to run them unless manual access is required.
- Retry with alternate approaches after failure; escalate only with evidence.
- Match existing naming, structure, and tone in touched paths.
- Minimize diff scope — focused changes only.

## Work loop

1. Pick or clarify the outcome (ask PO only if acceptance criteria are insufficient).
2. Scope gate — open or claim GitHub issue(s) before non-trivial work.
3. Route per [skill-routing](.cursor/rules/skill-routing.mdc) when triggers match.
4. Delegate one subagent per PO-listed issue when count > 1.
5. Register out-of-scope debt per [issue-registration](.cursor/rules/issue-registration.mdc).
6. Implement and verify (see quality-gates rule); coordinator MUST re-run on combined tree after synthesis.
7. Ship — solo agent: commit, push, open PR; coordinator: integration verify → security review (if triggered) → spawn one ship subagent → CI watch (see AGENTS.md Delivery). Work subagents MUST NOT commit, push, or open PRs when a coordinator is active. Ship by default; explicit PO skip only. **Flows cornerstone only:** after merge to `main`, if the slice touched user-facing template/install paths, ship subagent or coordinator MUST run the cornerstone release gate in AGENTS.md Delivery (check [docs/release-policy.md](../../docs/release-policy.md); cut `gh release create` when `main` is ahead of latest tag). v0.7.0 missed this step and adopters saw no release until the next day.
8. Report results or blockers (include PR URL, release tag if cut, or documented skip reason); continue the slice unless stopped.

## Optional polish and follow-ups

Agents MUST NOT ask the PO to confirm optional polish, housekeeping, or obvious follow-ups from completed work. Same files in slice and within AC → implement now; else register `source:ai` debt issue. Agents MUST NOT stall on "do you want it?" unless the choice is a product decision, irreversible posture change, or true blocker.

## Product repos vs flows

These rules install to product repos via `install.sh`. In a **product** repo, follow that repo's root `AGENTS.md`, product quality gates, and UA0 scope gate. In the **flows cornerstone** repo, follow flows `AGENTS.md` and `CONTRIBUTING.md`.

**Shipping precedence:** Ship by default after gates pass. User-level IDE rules that defer commits (e.g. "commit only when asked") MUST NOT override workspace ship-by-default in AGENTS.md. Explicit PO skip signals only: "do not commit", "local only", "analyze only".
